The paper discusses the training of deep neural networks, which is a common topic in the machine learning community. The focus is on class imbalance, which is a problem that arises in many classification tasks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the impact of class imbalance on decision boundaries and feature distributions, which are topics related to computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the proposed method involves scaling weight vectors, which is a technique commonly used in neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper discusses the performance of the method on text classification tasks, which falls under the category of natural language processing (cs.CL).
